  State & refs:
  - currentChangePos: number — -1 means no selection; 0-based index into changeIndex
  - rowRefs: MutableRefObject<(HTMLTableRowElement | null)[]> — keyed by unified row index so refs remain correct regardless of whether unchanged rows are hidden

  changeIndex memo — array of unified row indices for non-unchanged rows, rebuilt only when unifiedRows changes

  visibleRows — now carries { row, unifiedIndex } so each rendered row knows its position in the unified array for ref assignment and highlight detection

  navigateNext / navigatePrev — useCallback wrapped, wrap around at both ends, call scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth', block: 'center' })

  Keyboard shortcuts (registered via useEffect, cleaned up on unmount):
  - F7 → next change
  - Shift+F7 → previous change
  - Alt+ArrowDown → next change
  - Alt+ArrowUp → previous change

  Reset effect — clears currentChangePos to -1 and wipes rowRefs whenever result changes (new diff run)

  Navigation widget — sits in the summary bar at the far right: ↑ button | counter text | ↓ button. Counter shows "25 changes" initially, "Change X of 25" once navigation starts.
  Buttons have hover highlight and are disabled (opacity 0.3) when no changes exist.

  Current change highlight — outline: 2px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.55) with outlineOffset: -2px on the active <tr> — draws inside the row border without affecting layout.
